The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: The rate of inflation shot up to a four-month-high of 5.26 per cent for the week ended October 14 mainly due to increase in prices of food and manufactured items. The recent upward inflation trend is likely to put pressure on interest rates as RBI had raised its two key short term interest rates by 0.25 per cent in July to manage inflation. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Indian business confidence index (BCI) for July-September rose 7.6 per cent to 152.5 from 141.7 in the previous quarter on the back of a booming stock market, fall in oil prices and strong growth, the National Council for Applied Economic Research (NCAER) said.

 Mumbai, Oct. 27: Sebi has allowed non resident Indians (NRIs), foreign citizens and other entities based abroad to obtain permanent account number (PAN) for trading in the market on the basis of passport and a copy of a bank account in the country of residence. 

 Mumbai, Oct. 27: The Reserve Bank (RBI) has asked non-banking financial companies (NBFCs) to give 30-day public notice before effecting any change in their management or control structure. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 27: Reliance Communications and MTNL have lost the race for a telecom license bid in Kenya, where a Palestinian company is understood to have bagged the deal, sources said.




